for i in range(int(input())):
    data = input().split()
    x1 = int(data[0])
    x2 = int(data[1])
    x3 = int(data[2])
    v1 = int(data[3])
    v2 = int(data[4])
    t1 = (x3 - x1) / v1
    t2 = (x2 - x3) / v2
    if t1 == t2:
        print('Draw')
    if t1 > t2:
        print('Kefa')
    if t1 < t2:
        print('Chef')

for i in range(int(input())):
    (a, b, c, d, e) = map(int, input().split())
    x = abs(a - c) / d
    y = abs(b - c) / e
    print('Chef' if x < y else 'Kefa' if y < x else 'Draw')
